David Beckham has had a statue of himself unveiled in Los Angeles as he attended the LA Galaxy’s 2-1 win over the Chicago Fire on the opening day of the 2019 MLS season. The former England captain played for LA Galaxy between 2007 and 2012 during the twilight years of his stellar career, leading them to two championships, and he is still held in high regard in California. During a special ceremony ahead of the game in California, Beckham’s statue was unveiled as he was joined by wife Victoria at a special ceremony.